The paper deals with data structures and algorithms for path and ancestor queries on trees with multidimensional weight vectors. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). The paper also involves computational geometry, as it deals with orthogonal range queries, which fall under the purview of cs.CG (Computational Geometry). The paper also involves some aspects of data mining, which could place it under cs.DM (Data Mining). Additionally, the paper deals with databases, which could place it under cs.DB (Databases). Finally, the paper involves some aspects of artificial intelligence, which could place it under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence).
